DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260325T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260325T140000
DTSTAMP:20260324T234937
CREATED:20260220T230027Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260220T230028Z
UID:10030930-1774443600-1774447200@www.phinneycenter.org
SUMMARY:Oral Peptides
DESCRIPTION:Peptides are amino acids that work on proteins in your body\, and are one of the hottest topics in healthcare right now. This talk with Dr. Connie Amundsen provides answers to your questions about oral peptides: how do they differ from injected peptides such as GLP-1 receptor agonists (Wegovy\, Ozempic)\, how do they work\, are they safe\, what conditions are commonly treated\, are they affordable\, and how long does it take to see results? RSVP: 206.297.0875. \nWednesday\, March 25\, 1-2pm. GSC. Free.
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/oral-peptides/
LOCATION:Greenwood Senior Center\, 525 N. 85th St.\, Seattle\, WA\, 98103\, United States
CATEGORIES:GSC Featured,Senior Events
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://media.phinneycenter.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/20145805/Peptides.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Greenwood Senior Center":MAILTO:gsc@phinneycenter.org
END:VEVENT
